- Half decaf, half black,
with an extra shot,

15:18.047 --> 15:23.357
and a red velvet
banana cake pop...

15:23.400 --> 15:25.881
por favor.

15:28.275 --> 15:29.885
Merci.

15:29.929 --> 15:33.062
[funky jazz music]

15:33.106 --> 15:37.632
♪

15:37.675 --> 15:39.590
Shit.

15:39.634 --> 15:42.028
God damn it.

15:42.071 --> 15:49.122
♪

16:05.747 --> 16:09.011
Where the fuck is everybody?

16:09.055 --> 16:12.145
[peppy music]

16:12.188 --> 16:19.239
♪

16:22.372 --> 16:24.157
[music stops]

16:24.200 --> 16:27.421
[Orcus singing in French
in the distance]

16:32.730 --> 16:35.690
[continues singing,
playing piano]

16:35.733 --> 16:43.002
♪

16:54.404 --> 16:56.754
- [shrieking]
Help!

16:56.798 --> 16:58.713
Help!
[wails]

16:58.756 --> 17:02.412
Humperdonk!
Humperdonk!

17:02.456 --> 17:03.674
Flobbert!
[wails]

17:03.718 --> 17:06.895
Baballoon, Baballoon!

17:06.938 --> 17:08.897
[snarls]

17:08.940 --> 17:11.073
- You know,
if I wanted you dead,

17:11.117 --> 17:12.727
I'd have already made you

17:12.770 --> 17:15.164
bugger yourself
with that poker.

17:15.208 --> 17:17.601
- Why are you talking
like Elton John?

17:17.645 --> 17:19.386
- [imitating Blue]
Oh, sorry.

17:19.429 --> 17:22.389
Mister Bug, please!

17:22.432 --> 17:25.914
Don't hurt me, mister!

17:25.957 --> 17:27.568
[normal voice]
Is that better?

17:27.611 --> 17:29.309
- Much, yeah.

17:29.352 --> 17:31.833
- Blue...

17:31.876 --> 17:35.663
is dead, Louis.

17:35.706 --> 17:37.795
- You're Blue.
- No, no, no.

17:37.839 --> 17:40.581
I am Orcus...

17:40.624 --> 17:44.411
and I am so very excited

17:44.454 --> 17:46.891
to finally make
your acquaintance.

17:46.935 --> 17:49.198
[cork pops]

17:49.242 --> 17:51.200
Champagne?

17:51.244 --> 17:54.986
We've got a new,
bouncing bundle of joy

17:55.030 --> 17:58.381
on the way, don't we?

17:58.425 --> 18:02.777
But the mother-to-be,
she's run off.

18:02.820 --> 18:04.126
- How did you know?

18:04.170 --> 18:08.609
- Now, to show you
that I come in peace...

18:08.652 --> 18:12.047
I'm going to retrieve
Ms. Hanson for you.

18:12.091 --> 18:14.528
- That's impossible.

18:14.571 --> 18:16.356
Her ex is a super soldier.

18:16.399 --> 18:18.967
He must do Bar Method,
like, every day.

18:19.010 --> 18:20.882
- Oh, dear.

18:20.925 --> 18:22.971
Well...

18:23.014 --> 18:24.103
[glasses clinking]

18:24.146 --> 18:26.279
There is strength
in numbers.

18:26.322 --> 18:30.370
[overlapping chatter,
cheering]

18:30.413 --> 18:33.373
[hip-hop music]

18:33.416 --> 18:40.162
♪

18:40.206 --> 18:41.642
And my friends here...

18:41.685 --> 18:44.949
they really don't mind
getting their hands dirty.

18:44.993 --> 18:50.520
♪

18:50.564 --> 18:53.219
[all cheering]

19:00.443 --> 19:02.184
- Where the hell
you think you're going?

19:02.228 --> 19:04.012
- Out.
- Out where?

19:04.055 --> 19:06.449
- To look for Bo Peep.
- The hell you are.

19:06.493 --> 19:08.321
You're gonna be here,
and we're gonna have

19:08.364 --> 19:10.453
a family lunch
like normal people.

19:10.497 --> 19:12.629
- You're not the boss of me.
- I'm the--

19:12.673 --> 19:15.023
- What if I don't want to be
a part of this family?

19:15.066 --> 19:17.025
- You don't get to pick
your family, Hap.

19:17.068 --> 19:20.071
Somehow Hailey had you--
invented you--

19:20.115 --> 19:22.987
It doesn't matter.
You're stuck here with us.

19:23.031 --> 19:24.772
And by the way...
- What?

19:24.815 --> 19:26.513
- Forget about it.
- What? Say it.

19:26.556 --> 19:28.428
It's about Bo, isn't it?

19:28.471 --> 19:31.518
- You wouldn't believe me
if I told you, pal.

19:31.561 --> 19:32.388
- Whatever.

19:32.432 --> 19:33.955
- [mockingly]
Whatever.

19:33.998 --> 19:36.044
Yeah.

19:36.087 --> 19:38.438
[squeak]

19:39.830 --> 19:41.005
You're gonna sit there

19:41.049 --> 19:42.355
and pretend to have lunch
with this family.

19:42.398 --> 19:45.532
- Fine, but I'm gonna
listen to my Beats.

19:45.575 --> 19:48.752
[pop music playing]
- Turn down that--Oh, God.

19:48.796 --> 19:50.232
- Ta-da!

19:50.276 --> 19:52.887
- Oh.

19:52.930 --> 19:56.064
- Looks like
a pile of puke!

19:56.107 --> 19:58.284
- And, uh...

19:58.327 --> 20:01.591
what is that you call
this tasty dish?

20:01.635 --> 20:04.377
- Orange juice risotto.

20:04.420 --> 20:06.901
- [sighs]

20:06.944 --> 20:10.818
[coughs, gags]

20:10.861 --> 20:12.254
Tangy.
- [giggles]

20:12.298 --> 20:14.909
- Glad you like it, Arlo.
- Mm-hmm.

20:14.952 --> 20:17.128
- Why do you keep
calling him Arlo?

20:17.172 --> 20:18.869
- Didn't I ever tell you
about the time

20:18.913 --> 20:20.262
I lost my wedding ring?

20:20.306 --> 20:22.264
- You never talked about Dad.

20:22.308 --> 20:24.310
- Well, your dad took me

20:24.353 --> 20:26.355
to eat crabs
by the Jersey Shore,

20:26.399 --> 20:28.923
and I banged my finger
with one of those mallets,

20:28.966 --> 20:30.968
so I had to take
my wedding ring off

20:31.012 --> 20:32.448
so I could run it
under cold water.

20:32.492 --> 20:34.581
And I forgot my ring
in the bathroom.

20:34.624 --> 20:36.757
- The restaurant--they said
that no one had found it,

20:36.800 --> 20:39.368
but I smelled a rat.

20:39.412 --> 20:41.414
- Your dad checked the log
and found the woman

20:41.457 --> 20:43.198
who was cleaning
the bathroom that day,

20:43.242 --> 20:45.461
then he scoured the pawnshops
in her neighborhood

20:45.505 --> 20:47.507
until he found my wedding ring.

20:47.550 --> 20:49.683
- But I was too late,
because...

20:49.726 --> 20:53.077
the ring had already been sold
to one Arlo Jeffers.

20:53.121 --> 20:56.037
[spoon clatters]

20:56.080 --> 20:58.300
So I paid him
an official police visit

20:58.344 --> 21:00.259
and told him that
the property had been stolen

21:00.302 --> 21:03.349
and he should return it...

21:03.392 --> 21:05.786
to its rightful owners.

21:05.829 --> 21:09.137
And, uh, unfortunately
he'd already had it engraved.

21:09.180 --> 21:12.140
[light music]

21:12.183 --> 21:13.968
♪

21:14.011 --> 21:16.797
- It read "Arlo plus Marie."

21:16.840 --> 21:18.973
- "Love forever."

21:19.016 --> 21:20.888
[dramatic music]

21:20.931 --> 21:24.152
- I-I'm feeling a little flush
from all that cooking.

21:24.195 --> 21:26.850
I'm gonna go splash
some water on my face.

21:26.894 --> 21:28.548
BRB.

21:30.158 --> 21:32.639
- [sighs]

21:32.682 --> 21:34.293
[door closes]

21:34.336 --> 21:35.381
- Yeah, I thought so.

21:35.424 --> 21:36.947
Look, your Mom and I
will do the dishes.

21:36.991 --> 21:38.209
Why don't you go upstairs
and watch TV?

21:38.253 --> 21:40.647
- It's okay, I'll help you.
- No, no, no.

21:40.690 --> 21:42.039
I-I insist.

21:42.083 --> 21:44.564
I'll tell you what, today is
"no chores for you" day.

21:44.607 --> 21:46.870
In fact, once your mom
and I are done,

21:46.914 --> 21:48.785
I-I'll take you
for a malted.

21:48.829 --> 21:50.526
- I don't know what that is.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.049
- Well, then you're gonna
find out.

21:52.093 --> 21:55.270
- [chuckles]
- Go follow her.

21:55.314 --> 21:58.665
Go and follow her.
- Oh, really?

21:58.708 --> 22:00.014
I don't get to listen
to any more

22:00.057 --> 22:01.885
of your sappy stories?

22:01.929 --> 22:04.540
- I'm gonna feed you
to a Rottweiler.

22:04.584 --> 22:06.890
[scoffs, stammers]

22:06.934 --> 22:09.023
- All better.
- Hey.

22:09.066 --> 22:11.460
- Where's Hailey?

22:13.157 --> 22:16.247
- Where is it?
- What, Nick?

22:16.291 --> 22:18.249
- Well, what do we have here?

22:18.293 --> 22:21.470
- Give that back.

22:21.514 --> 22:25.431
- What the--
[dishware shattering]

22:25.474 --> 22:27.694
Christ!

22:27.737 --> 22:29.522
♪

22:29.565 --> 22:33.656
- You got a lot of nerve
taking my shit from me!

22:33.700 --> 22:37.399
You were a junkie
for half our marriage!

22:37.443 --> 22:39.358
That's why
I stopped loving you.

22:39.401 --> 22:41.795
That's why I never
wanted you around Hailey,

22:41.838 --> 22:43.710
'cause you were a loser!

22:43.753 --> 22:47.235
- Jesus Christ, it's like
being married to Johnny Depp.

22:47.278 --> 22:49.063
- No!

22:49.106 --> 22:51.195
Get off me!

22:51.239 --> 22:52.588
I'm going back to Sonny.

22:52.632 --> 22:55.504
He's more of a man
than you'll ever be.

22:55.548 --> 22:57.158
♪

22:57.201 --> 22:59.073
- So you've seen his penis?

22:59.116 --> 23:01.771
- [screaming]
- [growls]

23:08.430 --> 23:10.954
- Your mom's a little bit
sick right now.

23:10.998 --> 23:13.304
Um, not in her body,

23:13.348 --> 23:16.525
but, uh, in her head.

23:16.569 --> 23:19.136
But probably soon
in her body, too.

23:19.180 --> 23:21.791
Uh, not serious.

23:21.835 --> 23:23.619
Um, although it's very serious.

23:23.663 --> 23:25.708
So we just need
to treat her gently

23:25.752 --> 23:28.232
and show her tough love.

23:31.061 --> 23:33.412
Got it?

23:36.023 --> 23:38.373
Ah, hell, let me just
show you.

23:47.164 --> 23:48.992
- Oh.

23:49.036 --> 23:50.864
Hi, honey.

23:50.907 --> 23:53.432
- She's fine.
- I'm fine.

23:53.475 --> 23:54.520
- Yeah.

23:54.563 --> 23:56.217
So I need you
to watch her for a sec

23:56.260 --> 23:59.655
while I take care
of some business.

23:59.699 --> 24:01.135
Think you can do that?

24:01.178 --> 24:03.442
- Uh-huh.
- Atta girl.

24:05.922 --> 24:07.968
Okay.

24:14.061 --> 24:16.846
- You look
quite striking, Louis.

24:16.890 --> 24:21.024
- Penguin suits really aren't
my thing, but I do, don't I?

24:21.068 --> 24:22.635
It's my wife's.

24:22.678 --> 24:23.984
She played Joel Grey

24:24.027 --> 24:27.030
in the unauthorized
"Cabaret" story.

24:27.074 --> 24:29.424
- Hmm.

24:31.818 --> 24:35.474
I do think you're going
to enjoy this opera.

24:36.910 --> 24:39.869
- [vocalizing]

24:39.913 --> 24:45.092
♪

24:45.135 --> 24:49.879
- Mephistopheles is trying
to tempt Faust.

24:49.923 --> 24:53.013
He offers to make
the old scholar young again,

24:53.056 --> 24:55.406
but only in exchange
for the old man's--

24:55.450 --> 24:56.886
[cell phone beeping]

24:56.930 --> 25:01.500
♪

25:01.543 --> 25:04.198
- Stop.
- [stops singing]

25:04.241 --> 25:05.982
- Give it.

25:06.026 --> 25:08.289
- [groans]

25:11.335 --> 25:13.903
- This is high art.

25:13.947 --> 25:15.339
The highest.

25:15.383 --> 25:17.907
But, no, you'd rather play--
what is it?

25:17.951 --> 25:19.735
"Critter Crush."

25:19.779 --> 25:22.085
- I was about to enter
the Centimorph Maze.

25:22.129 --> 25:25.480
- You are going to die one day.

25:25.524 --> 25:28.570
That is the only certainty
that you will ever have.

25:28.614 --> 25:31.355
All humans are armed
with this knowledge,

25:31.399 --> 25:35.272
but most of you just
piss your time away

25:35.316 --> 25:39.799
playing video games,
watching sports.

25:43.367 --> 25:45.979
Fame.
- Yes, what about it?

25:46.022 --> 25:47.328
- I can give it you.

25:47.371 --> 25:49.286
- No, I'm--I'm a pretty
big deal already, Mucus.

25:49.330 --> 25:52.115
- Orcus.
[hisses]

25:52.159 --> 25:55.118
- Tomato, potato.

25:55.162 --> 25:59.079
- Your name can stand
besides those of...

25:59.122 --> 26:02.299
Kangaroo, Rogers...

26:02.343 --> 26:04.780
the Wiggles...
- [chuckles]

26:04.824 --> 26:09.089
- Or it could stand
amongst the greats...

26:09.132 --> 26:12.962
Lincoln, Lenin, King.

26:14.050 --> 26:15.312
Diana.

26:15.356 --> 26:17.445
- Oh, now we're talking.

26:19.403 --> 26:23.146
I like this guy way better
than that other guy.

26:23.190 --> 26:25.279
- Well...

26:25.322 --> 26:26.976
a great man like yourself

26:27.020 --> 26:30.153
deserves a better class
of chum.

26:30.197 --> 26:32.460
Don't you think?

26:34.636 --> 26:36.246
Please.

26:36.290 --> 26:39.641
- [singing in foreign language]

26:39.685 --> 26:42.775
♪

26:44.385 --> 26:46.517
- You sit on this spot,
you do not move.

26:46.561 --> 26:48.694
You see anyone coming,
you get me.

26:48.737 --> 26:50.696
You hear a strange noise--
a dog howling,

26:50.739 --> 26:52.785
a car door slamming--
you get me.

26:52.828 --> 26:53.786
Got it?
- Got it.

26:53.829 --> 26:55.831
- Good. Questions?
- Just one.

26:55.875 --> 26:57.659
- Go.

26:57.703 --> 27:00.662
- [crying]
Why hasn't she called me?

27:00.706 --> 27:03.360
- [softly] Damn it.
- [whining]

27:03.404 --> 27:05.188
- Did she say she'd call?
- Yeah!

27:05.232 --> 27:06.886
We--we had an amazing night,

27:06.929 --> 27:09.018
but she had to get back
to work early, so--

27:09.062 --> 27:11.760
She told me
she'd call and--

27:11.804 --> 27:13.109
- Um, hey, hey.

27:13.153 --> 27:14.981
Come here, buddy.
Sit down.

27:15.024 --> 27:18.201
[sighs] Now, I know I'm gonna
regret asking this.

27:18.245 --> 27:20.856
[inhales deeply]
How was it?

27:20.900 --> 27:23.337
- How--how was what?
The lovemaking?

27:23.380 --> 27:24.643
- Please stop saying that.

27:24.686 --> 27:26.688
- It was Earth-shattering.
It was mind-bending.

27:26.732 --> 27:30.387
Who knew so much excitement,
so much joy and emotion

27:30.431 --> 27:34.478
could be packed
into one intense minute?

27:35.392 --> 27:36.785
- One minute?

27:36.829 --> 27:38.221
- Is that bad?

27:38.265 --> 27:40.354
- It is the second-smallest
measure of time on Earth.

27:40.397 --> 27:43.705
- Well, maybe there were
a few snags.

27:43.749 --> 27:45.446
- My eye!

27:45.489 --> 27:47.491
- I swear this has
never happened before.

27:47.535 --> 27:49.015
I had too much candy.

27:49.058 --> 27:50.233
- [shrieks]
Ouch!

27:50.277 --> 27:52.322
I said watch the teeth!

27:52.366 --> 27:54.237
- [grunts]
I-I can't help it.

27:54.281 --> 27:55.978
I'm all teeth.

27:58.154 --> 28:01.592
- That--that's horrifying.
- Yeah, you're telling me.

28:01.636 --> 28:04.595
- Yeah, look, but, hey, it's
happened to the best of us.

28:04.639 --> 28:06.510
- I don't care
about the best of us.

28:06.554 --> 28:09.252
I care about Bo Peep!
- Oh, God, stop, all right?

28:09.296 --> 28:11.080
All right, listen,
you want my advice?

28:11.124 --> 28:12.908
- Love-life advice from the guy

28:12.952 --> 28:15.606
whose wife is bound
and gagged in our basement.

28:15.650 --> 28:18.261
- First of all, take it down
a notch with the attitude.

28:18.305 --> 28:19.959
Second of all, forget about Bo.

28:20.002 --> 28:23.876
Get out there, find a fine
piece of imaginary ass,

28:23.919 --> 28:27.357
and tap it, hard!

28:27.401 --> 28:29.620
- I-I don't get it.

28:29.664 --> 28:31.448
- Hap, years from now,

28:31.492 --> 28:33.407
you'll be eating a bucket
of fried chicken

28:33.450 --> 28:34.930
watching a terrible rom-com

28:34.974 --> 28:37.628
rented from your local
Hollywood Video with your wife.

28:37.672 --> 28:40.196
You'll excuse yourself
to go to the bathroom

28:40.240 --> 28:42.416
and promptly stalk Bo
on social media.

28:42.459 --> 28:43.765
Now, with any luck,

28:43.809 --> 28:46.550
her boyfriend won't be
wildly successful,

28:46.594 --> 28:49.118
handsome, hung like a mule.

28:49.162 --> 28:50.772
The point is...

28:50.816 --> 28:53.644
it'll all be water
under the bridge soon enough,

28:53.688 --> 28:55.124
so...

28:55.168 --> 28:57.866
in the meantime, why not...

28:57.910 --> 29:01.261
put our heads down
and focus on our work?

29:01.304 --> 29:03.959
- What work?

29:04.003 --> 29:05.874
- Looking out that window.

29:07.093 --> 29:09.225
- Sometimes I wish we could
just go back

29:09.269 --> 29:12.141
to the way things used to be.

29:12.185 --> 29:15.144
You know, before...

29:15.188 --> 29:17.146
everything happened.

29:17.190 --> 29:19.496
- I wish that, too...

29:19.540 --> 29:21.107
all the time.

29:21.150 --> 29:24.806
- We were good when it was just
the two of us, weren't we?

29:24.850 --> 29:26.982
Our biggest problem
was figuring out

29:27.026 --> 29:29.115
what movie to watch.

29:29.158 --> 29:32.161
And then you'd put
all your M&Ms in the popcorn,

29:32.205 --> 29:35.208
and they'd get all gooey.
- You thought that was gross.

29:35.251 --> 29:36.949
- I miss it.

29:38.385 --> 29:41.083
I want to do it all again.

29:41.127 --> 29:42.998
- Me too.

29:43.042 --> 29:44.826
- Maybe things
can be that way again

29:44.870 --> 29:47.176
without anyone
getting in our way.

29:47.220 --> 29:49.570
- How?
- Let's get out of here.

29:49.613 --> 29:51.137
Just the two of us.

29:51.180 --> 29:55.010
We'll move far away, and no one
will ever bother us.

29:58.187 --> 30:00.799
I just need you to untie me.

30:04.498 --> 30:06.413
You're doing
the right thing, baby.

30:06.456 --> 30:07.893
You can trust me.

30:07.936 --> 30:11.157
If you can't trust your
parents, who can you trust?

30:11.200 --> 30:14.160
[tense music]

30:14.203 --> 30:15.335
♪

30:15.378 --> 30:17.598
What is it?

30:17.641 --> 30:20.122
- All you've done is lie to me.

30:20.166 --> 30:21.863
- Yeah, but I explained--

30:21.907 --> 30:25.780
- From the beginning,
before all this.

30:25.824 --> 30:27.347
You never told me about Dad.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.871
- Well, that was
for your own good.

30:29.915 --> 30:31.307
♪

30:31.351 --> 30:33.744
Hailey Louise Hanson,
you get over here right now

30:33.788 --> 30:36.660
and get these off me.

30:36.704 --> 30:39.054
- This is for your own good.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.273
Dad says so.

30:40.316 --> 30:43.232
- Oh, your wonderful dad...

30:43.276 --> 30:45.234
who abandoned us...

30:45.278 --> 30:47.758
penniless and alone?

30:47.802 --> 30:49.586
Who doesn't care about us?

30:49.630 --> 30:53.416
Who's a drunk,
an addict, a killer?

30:53.460 --> 30:54.896
I sacrificed
everything for you,

30:54.940 --> 30:56.506
and this is how you thank me?

30:56.550 --> 30:57.725
- Hailey.

30:57.768 --> 31:00.902
- [exhales deeply]
- Go upstairs.

31:00.946 --> 31:02.643
Go upstairs.

31:02.686 --> 31:05.515
- Let me go!
- No.

31:05.559 --> 31:07.953
Upstairs, now.

31:07.996 --> 31:09.998
Go on.

31:10.869 --> 31:14.437
- You can't keep me down here
tied up like a dog.

31:14.481 --> 31:16.265
- No? What?
What are you gonna do?

31:16.309 --> 31:17.919
Run back to Sonny Shine?

31:17.963 --> 31:21.357
Go get high with the man who
kidnapped your own daughter?

31:21.401 --> 31:24.012
- Sonny Shine kidnapped me?

31:24.056 --> 31:25.535
[somber music]

31:25.579 --> 31:27.363
Answer.

31:27.407 --> 31:30.062
Did Sonny Shine kidnap me?

31:30.105 --> 31:31.324
- Tell her, Nick.

31:31.367 --> 31:33.456
♪

31:33.500 --> 31:35.110
- Yeah.

31:35.154 --> 31:38.461
- Why isn't he in jail?

31:38.505 --> 31:41.290
- Sometimes bad guys
don't get caught.

31:41.334 --> 31:43.945
- Why didn't you tell me?

31:43.989 --> 31:46.513
- I thought I was doing
what was best for you.

31:46.556 --> 31:49.124
- Oh, you know
what's best for me?

31:49.168 --> 31:51.257
You don't know
anything about me.

31:51.300 --> 31:53.172
- Nick?
- Shut up!

31:53.215 --> 31:54.564
Not you, not you, him.

31:54.608 --> 31:57.524
- I hate you both.

31:57.567 --> 31:59.439
- Hailey.
- Great work, Daddy.

31:59.482 --> 32:01.876
No wonder she hates you.
- Nick, Nick!

32:01.920 --> 32:04.226
- What the fuck
do you want, Happy?

32:07.055 --> 32:08.665
Hailey!

32:08.709 --> 32:11.538
[dark music]

32:11.581 --> 32:13.105
Hailey!

32:13.148 --> 32:14.758
♪

32:14.802 --> 32:17.500
What the--
[men shouting]

32:17.544 --> 32:20.329
[grunts, shouts]

32:20.373 --> 32:22.592
- [screaming]

32:22.636 --> 32:27.989
♪

32:28.033 --> 32:29.512
[men shouting]

32:29.556 --> 32:32.515
[suspenseful music]

32:32.559 --> 32:38.782
♪

32:38.826 --> 32:41.524
- [screaming]

32:41.568 --> 32:46.007
♪

32:46.051 --> 32:47.356
Happy!

32:47.400 --> 32:49.619
Hailey ran off!
Follow her!

32:49.663 --> 32:52.535
[shouts]

32:52.579 --> 32:55.190
- [panting]
Hailey!

32:55.234 --> 33:01.196
♪

33:01.240 --> 33:03.024
[all shouting]

33:03.068 --> 33:05.200
- Later, sucker.

33:05.244 --> 33:08.377
♪

33:08.421 --> 33:10.771
[light buzzing]

33:10.814 --> 33:13.992
[The Dandy Warhol's "Forever"]

33:14.035 --> 33:19.736
♪

33:19.780 --> 33:21.564
- [spits]

33:21.608 --> 33:23.566
Ha ha...
[growls]

33:23.610 --> 33:30.573
♪

33:30.617 --> 33:34.403
- ♪ All that I seem to find

33:34.447 --> 33:35.926
♪

33:35.970 --> 33:39.582
♪ I could make it mine

33:39.626 --> 33:43.064
♪ But I'd end up
inside my head ♪

33:43.108 --> 33:45.936
♪

33:45.980 --> 33:49.070
- [shouting in slow-motion]

33:49.114 --> 33:51.246
♪

33:51.290 --> 33:55.598
♪ Now there's a gong
in the sky that's bright ♪

33:55.642 --> 33:57.296
♪

34:01.082 --> 34:04.346
- ♪ Spring is here,
and the air is clear ♪

34:04.390 --> 34:06.783
♪ Chicks chirp,
cheep, cheep, cheep ♪

34:06.827 --> 34:10.483
♪ And hibernating animals

34:10.526 --> 34:12.485
♪ Awaken from their sleep

34:12.528 --> 34:14.008
[blade slicing,
monitor beeping rapidly]

34:14.052 --> 34:16.489
♪ But in all
of nature's beauty ♪

34:16.532 --> 34:18.708
♪ Great and small

34:18.752 --> 34:20.841
♪

34:20.884 --> 34:22.277
- Where am I?

34:22.321 --> 34:26.020
- ♪ I just saw
the strangest thing of all ♪

34:26.064 --> 34:27.326
♪

34:27.369 --> 34:30.329
- OMG.

34:30.372 --> 34:33.636
Better than I could have
ever dreamed.

34:33.680 --> 34:36.335
- ♪ The Easter Bunny
has lost his bounce ♪

34:36.378 --> 34:39.860
♪ And has to borrow
a bicycle ♪

34:39.903 --> 34:41.601
- Oh, my...

34:41.644 --> 34:43.690
What have you done to me?

34:43.733 --> 34:45.866
- Like a bunny.
- [whimpers]

34:45.909 --> 34:47.911
- Like a big, big bunny.

34:47.955 --> 34:50.871
Oh, I love, love, love.

34:50.914 --> 34:52.916
- [whimpers]
- Oh...

34:52.960 --> 34:55.919
the plans I have for you.

34:55.963 --> 34:58.879
Mm.
- You're insane.

34:58.922 --> 35:01.882
- Who, me?
[laughing]

35:01.925 --> 35:04.754
[joyful music continues]

35:04.798 --> 35:06.626
Maybe.
- [gasps]

35:06.669 --> 35:08.193
[door closes]

35:08.236 --> 35:10.195
[foreboding music]

35:10.238 --> 35:12.371
- [grunts]
[IV tube pops]

35:12.414 --> 35:15.156
♪

35:15.200 --> 35:17.637
[monitor beeping rapidly]

35:17.680 --> 35:19.987
[grunts]

35:20.030 --> 35:22.729
[grunting]

35:22.772 --> 35:25.384
[breathing heavily]

35:25.427 --> 35:30.258
♪

35:30.302 --> 35:32.739
Ah!

35:32.782 --> 35:39.789
♪

35:42.923 --> 35:45.882
[eerie chirping, warbling]

35:45.926 --> 35:49.277
♪

35:49.321 --> 35:52.193
Are you talking to me?

35:52.237 --> 35:54.413
[Wishees continue chirping]

35:54.456 --> 35:56.458
♪

35:56.502 --> 35:59.679
Who's Orcus?

35:59.722 --> 36:00.854
[door clangs open loudly]

36:00.897 --> 36:03.552
- Oh, you got a lot of nerve

36:03.596 --> 36:07.556
just--just strutting in here
like Travolta.

36:09.645 --> 36:11.125
- What--what is that?

36:11.169 --> 36:12.909
That conjunctivitis?

36:12.953 --> 36:15.782
Someone been farting
on your face?

36:15.825 --> 36:18.350
You know, should be you in here

36:18.393 --> 36:19.829
looking an orangutan.

36:19.873 --> 36:22.963
All you had to do was just
get rid of some kids.

36:23.006 --> 36:24.443
Just one job.

36:24.486 --> 36:27.837
But, no, you was
out gallivanting.

36:27.881 --> 36:30.275
Where? Why? How? What?

36:30.318 --> 36:32.146
- I was told to come see you.

36:32.190 --> 36:33.582
- "Told"?

36:33.626 --> 36:36.281
Told by who?

36:36.324 --> 36:39.109
- I don't really know.

36:39.153 --> 36:41.155
- Yeah, well, you seen me.

36:41.199 --> 36:42.896
Now get lost.

36:44.332 --> 36:47.814
Get lost. Take a walk.
Fuck off.

36:47.857 --> 36:49.468
♪

36:49.511 --> 36:52.297
[eerie rumbling,
metal screeching]

36:52.340 --> 36:54.995
[as Orcus]
Just a moment, please.

36:55.038 --> 37:01.480
♪

37:01.523 --> 37:03.656
Please sit down.

37:03.699 --> 37:05.005
♪

37:05.048 --> 37:06.833
I beg you.

37:06.876 --> 37:08.095
Please.

37:08.138 --> 37:11.664
♪

37:11.707 --> 37:13.622
You've met my friends.

37:13.666 --> 37:15.233
[Wishees chirping]

37:15.276 --> 37:17.844
They told me you were
coming to see me.

37:17.887 --> 37:19.672
They like you.

37:19.715 --> 37:22.675
So do I.

37:22.718 --> 37:24.677
- I think that one...

37:24.720 --> 37:28.115
or both of us might be having
a schizophrenic episode.

37:28.158 --> 37:30.857
- [laughs]

37:30.900 --> 37:35.253
We are about to embark
on a long journey, you and I--

37:35.296 --> 37:40.127
a journey that will affect
the history of mankind...

37:40.170 --> 37:43.348
and not for the better.

37:43.391 --> 37:45.959
We're going to kill
Sonny Shine.

37:46.002 --> 37:48.353
[suspenseful music]

37:48.396 --> 37:51.704
How does that sound?

37:51.747 --> 37:53.053
- Go on.

37:53.096 --> 37:55.273
[knocking on door]

38:06.762 --> 38:09.069
[suspenseful music]

38:09.112 --> 38:12.202
- [crying softly]

38:12.246 --> 38:14.814
- There, there, little lamb.

38:14.857 --> 38:21.299
♪

38:24.389 --> 38:26.391
Come inside.

38:26.434 --> 38:27.914
- Oh, hell, no.

38:27.957 --> 38:29.785
♪

38:29.829 --> 38:32.048
[door slams]

38:32.092 --> 38:34.268
♪

38:34.312 --> 38:36.923
[panting]
Nick, Nick!

38:36.966 --> 38:38.794
♪

38:38.838 --> 38:40.448
Nick?

38:40.492 --> 38:41.884
Nick?

38:41.928 --> 38:43.233
Nick.

38:43.277 --> 38:45.105
- [groans]

38:45.148 --> 38:47.281
- Nick, you're alive!

38:47.325 --> 38:49.501
♪

38:49.544 --> 38:51.764
- [exhales sharply]
Where's Hailey?

38:51.807 --> 38:54.941
- It's bad, Nick.
She's with the bunny-eye guy.

38:54.984 --> 39:02.035
♪

39:08.955 --> 39:15.701
♪

39:19.835 --> 39:21.620
♪

39:21.663 --> 39:24.318
- I guess this means
we're off the wagon.

39:24.362 --> 39:27.321
♪

39:27.365 --> 39:30.368
- You're goddamn right.

39:30.411 --> 39:31.978
[gun cocks]
